H0.text: Which daily newspaper was founded in 1903 by Alfred Harmsworth as a 'newspaper for women, run by women'. The Daily Mirror

H1.text: Which daily newspaper was founded in 1903 by Alfred Harmsworth as a 'newspaper for women, run by women'. The Daily Mail

H2.text: Which daily newspaper was founded in 1903 by Alfred Harmsworth as a 'newspaper for women, run by women'. The Times

H3.text: Which daily newspaper was founded in 1903 by Alfred Harmsworth as a 'newspaper for women, run by women'. The Scurra

A4.text: The Daily Mirror was launched on 2 November 1903 by Alfred Harmsworth (later Lord Northcliffe) as a newspaper for women, run by women.
